The problem involves finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\), where \(Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8\) are the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\).

Given \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\), the probability that a single observation is less than 27.3 is \(P(X < 27.3) = 0.7\). Since the distribution is continuous, \(P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(Y_7 \leq 27.3)\).

The event \(Y_7 \leq 27.3\) occurs if at least seven of the eight observations are less than or equal to 27.3. Let \(N\) be the number of observations \(\leq 27.3\). Then \(N\) follows a binomial distribution with parameters \(n = 8\) and \(p = 0.7\).

Thus,  
\[P(Y_7 \leq 27.3) = P(N \geq 7) = P(N = 7) + P(N = 8).\]

Calculate the probabilities:  
\[P(N = 7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3) = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3,\]  
\[P(N = 8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 = (0.7)^8.\]

Compute the values:  
\[(0.7)^7 = 0.0823543,\]  
\[P(N = 7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 0.19765032,\]  
\[(0.7)^8 = 0.05764801,\]  
\[P(N = 8) = 0.05764801.\]

Sum the probabilities:  
\[P(N \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833.\]

Rounding 0.25529833 to three significant figures gives 0.255.

The final answer is a probability and has no unit.

