The problem requires a lower bound for \(P(|Y / n - 0.25| < 0.05)\) when \(Y\) follows a binomial distribution \(b(n, 0.25)\) and \(n = 500\).

Using Chebyshev's inequality, a lower bound for the probability is given by:
\[
P\left(\left| \frac{Y}{n} - p \right| < \varepsilon \right) \geq 1 - \frac{p(1-p)}{n \varepsilon^2}
\]
where \(p = 0.25\), \(\varepsilon = 0.05\), and \(n = 500\).

