Define \(Y_1 = \min(X_1, X_2)\) and \(Y_2 = \max(X_1, X_2)\). The cost is \(Z = 2Y_1 + Y_2\).

The minimum of two independent exponential random variables with rate \(\lambda\) has an exponential distribution with rate \(2\lambda\). Thus, \(Y_1\) has mean \(E[Y_1] = 1/(2\lambda) = 1/(2 \times 0.5) = 1/1 = 1\).

Note that \(Y_1 + Y_2 = \min(X_1, X_2) + \max(X_1, X_2) = X_1 + X_2\). Therefore:
\[
