- \(Y_1 = \min(X_1, X_2)\) has an exponential distribution with rate \(2\lambda = 1\), so \(E[Y_1] = 1\).
- Since \(Y_1 + Y_2 = X_1 + X_2\), it follows that \(Z = 2Y_1 + Y_2 = Y_1 + (X_1 + X_2)\).
