Solution: Chebyshev's inequality states that for a random variable \(X\) with mean \(\mu\) and standard deviation \(\sigma\), the probability \(P(|X - \mu| \geq k\sigma) \leq \frac{1}{k^2}\) for any \(k > 0\).

Given:
